>>> from stdnum.ru import snils
>>> from stdnum.exceptions import *

Checks a valid SNILS number and its formatting behavior:

>>> snils.validate('148-481-255 85')
'14848125585'
>>> snils.format('14848125585')
'148-481-255 85'
>>> snils.compact(' 148 481 255 85 ')
'14848125585'
>>> snils.is_valid('148-481-255 85')
True

Invalid SNILS values raise the expected exceptions:

>>> snils.validate('148-481-255')  # too short
Traceback (most recent call last):
    ...
InvalidLength: ...
>>> snils.validate('148-481-255 xx')  # invalid characters
Traceback (most recent call last):
    ...
InvalidFormat: ...
>>> snils.validate('148-481-255 00')  # invalid checksum
Traceback (most recent call last):
    ...
InvalidChecksum: ...
